5:
Hey, welcome back! How's your
grandfather?
9:
Healthy enough to be yelling at me.
He's mad that I keep interrupting my
adventures with silly trips home.
12: Heh. That sounds like him, all right.
17:
I just thought it would be nice to see
each other... But, I guess he'll still be
kicking around for a while.
21:
If this is what Gramps wants, 
then I guess I need to make him 
proud.
24:
Why don't you tag along with us
tomorrow? We're going to
investigate some underwater ruins.
28: That sounds perfect! I'd love to!
34:
This is insane! So many man-made
objects at the bottom of the ocean...
How'd they all get here?
37:
Apparently the sea level rose a long
time ago and swallowed this
civilization whole. These ruins are
what's left of them.
40:
Wow! Do you think my world has
ancient ruins like these, too?
43:
I think it does. In the Farlands, 
if I remember correctly?
47:
Why don't you try asking your
gramps? He's into that sort of stuff,
right?
51:
Well, uh... Yeah, he told me that he
was a well-traveled adventurer in
his younger years.
55:
But, if you get him started, good luck
getting him to stop...
59:
...Huh. I guess we droned on a bit,
too.
81: Did I... Did I make the right choice?
89:
Oh, give me a break. I was just
passing through.
96:
It's just... Don't get me wrong. I'm
having a blast seeing new things
every day.
99:
But the more fun I have, 
the more I think about my gramps.
101:
I bet he would've wanted to be here
too.
107:
It's just... I stopped him from coming
along, right?
110:
I can't help but wonder if he resents
me now, you know?
116: Whoa, Kaiser! What's the big idea?!
120:
Probably sick of your wishy-washy
moping, just like I am.
123:
You know the guy. Just tell him
about your adventures next time
you see him. I'm sure he'd love to
hear stories from another world.
143:
Just look at me! I've never been
better!
145:
More importantly, what's the sack
for? Did you get sick of adventuring
and come home?
147:
No way! This here's a sack of
souvenirs.
150:
I've been all over the place.
Scorching deserts, endless oceans...
Even a city full of metal buildings!
152:
I could hardly believe what I was
seeing. You've never been anywhere
like that, have you?
154:
Hoho, sounds like somebody's been
on quite the journey.
156:
But that's still nothing compared to
what I've done! I bet you didn't know
that I once discovered the
legendary home of the Draconic
Guardian!
161:
Hahahaha! You've still got a long
way to go if you want to brag to me!
165:
Guess I should get back to it, then.
Make sure you take care of yourself,
Gramps.
167:
Hmph. Think less about others and
more about yourself!
171:
Yeah, yeah. Anyway, catch you later,
Gramps.
174:
...One last thing, Lemarque. Tell
meare you having fun?
178:
...Huh? Yeah, of course! I'll bring you
even better souvenirs next time!
182:
Haha... That's the spirit, Lemarque.
Spread your wings... and... fly free...
